What you’re really pointing at

There are at least three layers here:

1. Closed game (zero-sum approximation)

* fixed resources
* fixed players
* fixed time horizon
* clear winners/losers

This is Survivor, poker hands, finite contests.

⸻

2. Open game (positive/negative-sum potential)

* resources can expand
* players can enter/exit
* rules evolve
* cooperation + competition mix

This is business, culture, ecosystems.

⸻

3. Meta-layer (frame selection)

* who chose the boundary?
* what’s excluded?
* what happens if we widen the frame?

This is where your ZPC move lives.

⸻

Vesica Piscis insight (this is the key)

You brought up the vesica—and that’s actually the cleanest model here.

Two circles:

* each has its own “sum”
* each has its own rules

The overlap:

* creates shared space
* where new rules can exist
* where value can be co-created instead of divided

So:

Zero-sum lives inside each circle
Non-zero-sum emerges in the overlap

⸻

